OL,6,G1987 In the early hours of the
OL,7,Gmorning, a major storm hit the south
OL,8,Gof England. BBC Television Centre
OL,9,Glost its main power supply. Via a
OL,10,Gback-up generator NC1 (Network
OL,11,GControl for BBC One) kept BBC One on
OL,12,Gair, with an impromptu edition of BBC
OL,13,GBreakfast Time, presented by Nicholas
OL,14,GWitchell from the BBC One continuity
OL,15,Gstudio (NC1 Con), also known as The
OL,16,GBroom Cupboard by viewers of CBBC.
OL,17,GThe programme later switched to a
OL,18,Gtemporary studio.JTV-am was initially
OL,19,Gbroadcast from a small studio at
OL,20,GThames TV before power was restored
OL,21,Gat its main studios in Camden.
OL,22,GAlthough BBC Two was not due on air
OL,23,Guntil 9am, with Pages from Ceefax,
OL,24,Gfollowed by Daytime on Two at 9.30pm,
